@node "DoorStartUp" "DoorStartUp Sources"

                              @{b}DoorStartUp Sources
                             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Door StartUp sources will be available in C, ASM and Amiga E.
@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "Sources" "Doors + Sources as examples"

                                @{b}Doors + Sources
                               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

We will include example sources to show how to programm for FAME.

Currently exists:

 - FAMEMailHeader.FIM: Shows how to create your own MailHeader correctly.
                       Source in C.

 - FAMEWHO.FIM       : Shows how to access and use the FAMESemaphore.
                       Source in C.

All the sources will make as much use of the FAME.library as is possible.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "Problems" "What to do on problems"

                             @{b}What to do on problems
                            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

To receive fast help on problems write an e-mail or call our board.
We will also have to setup two mailing lists. One for all and one for
programmers only.
@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "Includes" "FAME Include files"

                               @{b}FAME Include files
                              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Following includes for FAME are available:

-FAMEDefine.h         - Only defines.
-FAMEDoorCommands.h   - FIM Door Command defines and short description.
-FAMEDoorDefines.h    - Defines as macros for Doors.
-FAMEDoorExpansion.h  - Often needed procedures. Will eventually be a lib.
-FAMEDoorProto.h      - The header file for the C Door StartUp source.
-FAMEPublic.h         - The entry point to the includes.
-FAMEPublicStructs.h  - Different structures of FAME.
-FAMEUserStructs.h    - User structures of FAME.

@endnode

